foliation.note: Numbering in pencil in the upper right-hand corner of the first leaf of each quire, possibly by M.R. James. Full foliation added after digitisation.

collation.p:
The manuscript comprises eighteen quires composed of eight leaves. Ff. 1-2 (the first a former pastedown) and 143-144 (the last a former pastedown) are flyleaves.
Quire 18 (ff. 1-8)
Quire 28 (ff. 9-16)
Quire 38 (ff. 17-24)
Quire 48 (ff. 25-32)
Quire 58 (ff. 33-40)
Quire 68 (ff. 41-48)
Quire 78 (ff. 49-56)
Quire 88 (ff. 57-64)
Quire 98 (ff. 65-72)
Quire 108 (ff. 73-80)
Quire 118 (ff. 81-88)
Quire 128 (ff. 89-96)
Quire 138 (ff. 97-104)
Quire 148 (ff. 105-112)
Quire 158 (ff. 113-120)
Quire 168 (ff. 121-128)
Quire 178 (ff. 129-136)
Quire 188 (ff. 137-144)

layout.seg: Two columns, 27 lines, frame and lines ruled in brown leadpoint. Pricked in the outer margins. Written above top line.

decoNote.p: Green and plain parchment initials (2-5 ll.), some incorporating geometric elements, others terminating in stylized leaf forms (e.g. f. 9v), alternating with red and plain parchment abstract initials (2-5 ll.) of the same style [e.g. f. 7v], for the opening to the preface and the main text of the Speculum, as well as at other principal openings within the first text.
Plain green and red initials (1 l.) for some of the paragraph openings in the second text.

note.p: Later addition at the end of the text (f. 142v): 'Istud carmen debet dici in primo die nouies, in secundo viiies...'.

'Deo gracias' inscribed in ink on f. 1v and erased note at foot of same leaf. Erased provenance inscription on f. 2r: 'Liber...' and old list of contents on f. 2v:
In hoc volumine continentur
Alwynus qui uocatur albinus (de Gregorii moralibus)
Item Excepciones (beati Gregorii pape) super cantica canticorum)

Followed by another list of contents in a 17th-century hand:
1. Albini speculum ex Gregorij moralibus.
2. Albini Exceptiones sententiarum Gregorij super Canticum Salomonis.
Hi duc non habentur inter opera impressa.

And the last content item in an earlier hand:
Exorcismus ad Febres expellendas.

15th-century note on f. 143v: 'byggbe hyegates vj miliaria ab vrbe london heneselde / domine dominus noster quam admirabile est nomen tuum in universa terra' followed by a transcription of the alphabet.
Occasional marginal notes, probably 14th century, in a hand similar to some marginalia found in Queens' College MS 16.

binding.p: Early 20-century, undyed goatskin? over original wooden boards on two sewing stations.

history.acquisition: Given to Queens' College Library in the early 1630s by Francis Tyndall Tyndall, Francis with a 17th-century inscription recording the gift at head of f. 3r): 'Donum Francisci Tindall armigeri'.

recordHist.source: This catalogue entry derives predominantly from data assembled for the Fitzwilliam Museum’s Cambridge Illuminations project (publication forthcoming) and draws on the description in M.R. James, A descriptive catalogue of the western manuscripts in the library of Queens’ College, Cambridge (Cambridge, 1905).

availability.p: For further information on the availability of the manuscript, please contact Queens' Old Library and Special Collections.
